  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-03-04",
    "date": "2021-04-14T15:42:20Z",
    "text": "Securing Inspector General Independence Act of 2021\n\nThis bill limits the circumstances under which the President or certain agency heads may remove an Inspector General or place an Inspector General on non-duty status.\n\nBefore an Inspector General may be removed, Congress must be given a detailed account of the reasons for the removal and the Inspector General shall remain on the job for 30 days while Congress considers those reasons."
  },
